    <div class="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
        <h3>Can I make this casserole ahead of time?</h3>
        <p>Yes, you can prepare the sweet potato mixture up to a day in advance and store it in the refrigerator. When you’re ready to bake, simply add the marshmallows and bake as directed.</p>

        <h3>Can I use dairy-free ingredients?</h3>
        <p>Absolutely! You can substitute the butter and milk with your favorite dairy-free alternatives, such as coconut oil and almond milk, to make this casserole completely dairy-free.</p>

        <h3>What can I use instead of marshmallows?</h3>
        <p>If you prefer not to use marshmallows, you can top the casserole with a gluten-free crumble made from oats, brown sugar, and butter. This adds a delightful crunch to the dish.</p>

        <h3>How do I store leftovers?</h3>
        <p>Leftovers can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. Reheat in the oven or microwave before serving.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>This gluten-free sweet potato casserole with marshmallow is a must-try for anyone looking to enjoy a classic holiday dish without the gluten. It’s easy to make, packed with flavor, and sure to be a hit at your next gathering. Whether you’re hosting a large family dinner or a small holiday feast, this casserole will bring warmth and joy to your table. So, gather your ingredients, preheat your oven, and get ready to create a dish that will become a new tradition in your home.</p>

